title: Tracking Alabama's commits: Watch DL Quinnen Williams return an interception for a touchdown
text:
Wenonah remained unbeaten with a 50-0 win over Dora on Friday, and Quinnen Williams was a big reason why.
Williams has terrorized backfields all season long, but showed off his agility with this interception return for a touchdown.
Playing just the first half, Williams had three quarterback hurries and three tackles. Here's the interception. Go here if the video doesn't work on your browser.

2016 COMMITS
Jalen Hurts, QB, Channelview, Texas (Channelview)
Hurts and Channelview lost 23-14 to North Shore. Hurts did throw a 15-yard touchdown pass in the game.
B.J. Emmons, RB, Morganton, N.C. (Freedom)
Emmons ran for touchdowns of 36, 7 and 46 yards in a 54-21 win over Watauga.
T.J. Simmons, WR, Pinson, Ala. (Clay-Chalkville)
Simmons had three receptions for 44 yards and a touchdown in the Cougars' 52-7 win over Shades Valley. He had a 24-yard rushing touchdown and seven pancake blocks.
Brendan Scales, TE, Ballwin, Mo. (Lafayette)
Lafayette lost 35-25 to St. Louis University. No stats were available on Scales.
Miller Forristall, TE, Cartersville, Ga. (Cartersville)
Forristall caught a 34-yard touchdown pass in Cartersville's 42-7 win over Ridgeland.
Jonah Williams, OL, Folsom, Calif. (Folsom)
Williams and Folsom beat Nevada Union 56-7.
Charles Baldwin, OL, Brooklyn, N.Y. (ASA College)
Baldwin and ASA lost 63-13 to Lackawanna.
Deonte Brown, OL, Decatur, Ala. (Austin)
Brown and Austin were off.
Chris Owens, OL, Arlington, Texas (Lamar)
Owens and Lamar beat Paschal 56-7.
Khalid Kareem, DE, Farmington, Mich. (Harrison)
Kareem and Harrison beat Farmington 13-12. No stats were available on Kareem.
Quinnen Williams, DL, Birmingham, Ala. (Wenonah)
Williams had a 42-yard interception return for a score, one batted ball, three QB hurries and three tackles in limited action in Wenonah's 50-0 blowout at Dora.
Kendell Jones, DL, Killeen, Texas (Shoemaker)
Jones and Shoemaker beat Midway 50-13.
Raekwon Davis, DL, Meridian, Miss. (Meridian)
Davis, who was selected to the Alabama-Mississippi All-Star game last week, and Meridian lost 24-21 to Oak Grove.
Riley Cole, LB, Oneonta, Ala. (Oneonta)
Cole and Oneonta beat J.B. Pennington 49-13, though Cole sat out with a minor knee injury.
Jaquan Yulee, LB, Chesapeake, Va. (Indian River)
Yulee and Indian River lost 15-14 to Oscar Smith.
Shawn Jennings, DB/ATH, Dadeville, Ala. (Dadeville)
Jennings is out for the season with a knee injury, but Dadeville lost 59-0 to leeds.
Joshua Perry, DB, Amite, La. (Amite)
Perry and Amite lost 21-20 to Sumner. No stats are available on Perry.
Eddy Pineiro, K, Miami, Fla. (ASA College)
Pineiro is not playing football this fall.
2017 COMMITS
Jake Fromm, QB, Warner Robins, Ga. (Houston County)
Houston County was off.
Cam Akers, QB/RB, Clinton, Miss. (Clinton)
Akers had two rushing touchdowns and a passing touchdowns in Clinton's 44-20 win over Murrah .
Najee Harris, RB, Antioch, Calif. (Antioch)
Harris had four carries for 126 yards and three touchdowns in Antioch's 53-14 win over Heritage. He scored on runs of 36, 4 and 71 yards .
D.D. Bowie, ATH, Morton, Miss. (Morton)
Bowie and Morton beat St. Andrews 62-14, though no stats are available on Bowie.
Chadarius Townsend, ATH, Tanner, Ala. (Tanner)
Townsend and Tanner dominated Southeastern 70-0, per the News Courier. Townsend had an 86-yard kickoff return for a score and threw a 58-yard touchdown pass.
Netori Johnson, OL, Ellenwood, Ga. (Cedar Grove)
Ellenwood beat McNair 20-0.
Alex Leatherwood, OL, Pensacola, Fla. (Washington)
Washington was off.
Xavier McKinney, DB, Roswell, Ga. (Roswell)
McKinney had this interception in Roswell's 45-7 win over Wheeler.
